<string name="help">
Pentomino is a a board game. 
BR

There are 13 pieces and the purpose of the game is to place them on the 8x8 board without overlapping. 
To place a piece on the board select it with a tap, and tap on the board cell where you want to place it.
To remove a piece from the board tap on it in the board.
The menu "Reset" clear the boards.
BR

The pieces can be rotated or flipped over with the buttons of the left.
BR

When the board is completed, 
the solution number is displayed in the text box.
If the solution is new it is added to the saved solutions.
Arrangements that differ by a 90 degree rotation or by a flip are not distinguished.
The number of solutions that you have found is shown in the title.
BR

With a completed board the button "View" lists the solutions that differ by at most 6 pieces from your solution.
If the board is partially filled the button "View" lists the solutions that match the pieces on the board.
Tapping on a number in the list displays the solution in the mini-board.
If you type a solution number in the text field, when the board is empty, the solution 
is shown in the main board.
BR

The saved solutions are stored in the file Android/data/com.pentomino/pentomino.txt (in the external storage).
BR

</string>

</resources>
